cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.CG, cs.MM, cs.AI 

This paper deals with computer vision techniques for estimating the shape and reflectance of an object from multiple images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves graphics techniques for rendering the object, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.GR (Computer Graphics). Additionally, the paper involves computational geometry techniques for estimating surface normals, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves machine learning techniques for estimating the BRDF, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves optimization techniques for estimating the shape and reflectance, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
